document.title: Maryland Physical Education Framework: Pre-Kindergarten Through High School

1A0CBF7276D24979B5DBB228F363101A.description:
Identifies how self-expression and physical
activity are related.

D3361E16396641198FEC2B2CEF1E9171.description:
Describes how moving
competently in a
physical activity setting
creates enjoyment.

5976171C80164E309784745D4FCC4AE8.description:
Recognizes that skills
will develop over time
with appropriate
practice.

E5003306C4EC49778739E67915CD22C4.description:
Recognizes individual
challenges and copes in
a positive way, such as
extending effort, asking
for help or feedback,
and/or modifying the
tasks.

401F9943EC954864ABCFE351A516CB11.description:
Identifies components
of physical activity that
provide opportunities
for reducing stress and
for social interaction.

96353756615F47ABA44181C00F6C332E.description:
Describes how being
physically active leads
to a healthy body.

18A7CC31670C48BE964B75EF09033997.description: Recognizes the Value of Physical Activity

12784D338B874942A901A9E7961A22D1.description:
Identifies the rules and
etiquette for activities.

7E75B00FFEE74A5A88AE2B77DD5A4FC2.description:
Cooperates with a small
group of classmates.

348DE3F6238F4BD687FE8D0DD083AC75.description:
Accepts differences
among classmates in
physical development,
maturation, and skill
level by providing
encouragement and
positive feedback.

463D795B399A4335A66B20168706F703.description:
Demonstrates self-responsibility by
implementing specific
corrective feedback to
improve performance.

314BF95F199745D381990ECA9DD82CD8.description:
Identifies and uses
appropriate strategies
to self-reinforce
positive fitness
behaviors.

1F069C6A79194DCEBBFA8F6E5773008F.description:
Exhibits personal
responsibility by using
appropriate etiquette,
demonstrating respect
for facilities, and
exhibiting safe
behaviors.

A6E9905FB8714211A6CD1F8EB2E8C850.description:
Employs correct
techniques and
methods of stretching.

91A0B39CAA9E4D0391C6FA231ECA73A3.description:
Sets and monitors a
self-selected physical
activity goal based on
current fitness level.

8806ED1CA39F4EF28D73BE7C30F9D64C.description:
Identifies the
components of skillrelated fitness.

27ABD466B6DF4F9CA4DD82AAAEC8094C.description:
Participates in a variety
of moderate-tovigorous physical
activities (cardio-kick,
step aerobics, aerobic
dance, recreational
team sports, outdoor
pursuits, or dance
activities).

C6A5EE49CADD42C0AD104B640E0909A4.description:
Identifies three
influences on physical
activity.

5233FC7EEC3A4F26A7CC694BA13DE30C.description: Health-Enhancing Level of Physical Activity and Fitness

6DCC987E6149404388359D6EC0AFC8A5.description:
Makes appropriate
decisions based on the
weather, level of
difficulty due to
conditions, or ability to
ensure the safety of self
and others.

00EDF7216DB84C9D971D7EA261C6B70D.description:
Varies application of
force during dance or
gymnastic activities.

0B5433DB67BE4A00B6962CCCAEB8D94F.description:
Identifies the correct
defensive play based on
the situation.

0EF77695E1FD45E58EA32002153F6EDE.description:
Identifies open spaces
and attempts to strike
object into that space.

34D8D379A14C4A83A7F8B9CBAE72B04D.description:
Selects appropriate shot
based on location of the
object in relation to the
target.

E2B2CB8C56B244FABD092070F53E0F72.description:
Reduces offensive
options for opponents
by returning to midcourt position.

2AD42B43DFCA4FB2A92CECEA34B6A83D.description:
Creates open space in
net or wall games with a
short-handled
implement by varying
force and direction.

BA961E70A35D409E8BF6FD52FA78434B.description:
Transitions from
offense to defense or
defense to offense by
recovering quickly.

05DD4EDBF1B24387B14DFB29DC976CDB.description:
Reduces open space by
not allowing the catch
(denial) or by allowing
the catch but not the
return pass.

B5304536A92C4CD3BDE108F03DD3A22F.description:
Reduces open space on
defense by making the
body larger and
reducing passing angles.

77F9410D02504A6F8149F9DFDC4E02C4.description:
Reducing Space -
Changing Size and
Shape

524772B67B854DD29A0EAA6E3C25F8C1.description:
Executes at least one of
the following offensive
tactics to create open
space: moves to open
space without the ball;
uses a variety of passes,
pivots and fakes; give
and go.

8203E9AD26054E8AAC447A3817AF1191.description:
Creates open space in
combination with
movement concepts.

5ADD431515C9427D846FEBFB17FD26BB.description:
Demonstrates correct
technique for basic
skills in one self-selected individual
performance activity.

FC4901B478D946C2B91C7E46CD099421.description:
Demonstrates correct
technique for basic
skills in one self-selected outdoor
activity.

50F7C533D94B411F9A9C8A6B9189E395.description:
Catches, with a mature
pattern, from different
trajectories, using a
variety of objects in
varying practice tasks
while using an
implement.

27E2AD1EC6DE49C4A23685A1B4E8A2B1.description:
Catching with a Short
or Long-Handled
Implement

99335ED567F348819D2D8C18072925F5.description:
Strikes a pitched ball
with an implement with
force in a variety of
practice tasks.

FFDC944EAB9541B89064C02262C7B587.description:
Demonstrates an ability
to propel an object for a
modified target game.

2429026279164C96B5FD258C5460B6D8.description:
Two-hand volleys with
control in a variety of
practice tasks.

B00ABE9E17B94EDFADC9F35F8FB68B89.description:
Forehand volleys with a
mature pattern and
control using a short-handled implement.

71E735AFB1CF4596BF397CF64BE340E2.description:
Transfers weight with
correct timing for a
striking pattern.

714E9AE032214E11AB42F17DD4234AE0.description:
Demonstrates the
mature form of the
forehand and backhand
strokes with a short-handled implement in
net games.

1CFDB5ED26344E159FE70D8F257818EF.description:
Strikes with a mature
overhand pattern in a
non-dynamic
environment for net or
wall games.

AE8A244914A14495AD570471936A0F45.description:
Performs an underhand
serve with control for
net and wall games.

DA912CD8884B4C47AB4210E62B3D3AB8.description:
Maintains defensive-ready position with
weight on balls of feet,
arms extended, and
eyes on midsection of
the offensive player.

978B919CC1994BFA87A31BDF7978015F.description:
Shoots on goal with
power in a dynamic
environment as
appropriate to the
activity.

56A059A1B87D4A9284D4C2EDFD73FC06.description:
Foot-dribbles or
dribbles with an
implement with control,
changing speed and
direction in a variety of
practice tasks.

3846F18F0E3F482D8AF53BFA19B6B37E.description:
Dribbles with dominant
hand using a change of
speed and direction in a
variety of practice
tasks.

16CAF28A71AD4B07A4443876ACA35ABA.description:
Performs the following
offensive skills without
defensive pressure:
pivot, give and go, and
fakes.

AFD94884570948DC9DA0C2467CA34293.description:
Performs pivots, fakes,
and jab steps designed
to create open space
during practice tasks.

55E4B9AEB4044047A59A636E01BA6D70.description:
Throws, while
stationary, a leading
pass to a moving
receiver.

86A62D2BAC6B44C99ECA4C157FFDE993.description:
Passes and receives
with hands while
changing direction and
speed with
competency.

3616891CDF094EDE860DCDD51B6AC145.description:
Catches a variety of
objects from different
trajectories with a
mature pattern in
varying practice tasks.

730E4314D7294F8DB2B90E8246992EC1.description:
Throws with a mature
pattern for distance or
power appropriate to
the practice task.

7A95CC42957B4B28AE17656397DF542B.description:
Demonstrates correct
rhythm and pattern for
one dance form.
